The keyword 'Roman' may cause issues in Microsoft Office applications. Style linking and/or font embedding for MS Word won't work.
(The keyword 'Roman' causes cross platform issues in Adobe InDesign, Jan. 2019)
More infos here:
Unified Monotype Weight Name Rules

Pass

Times New Roman Regular (times.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

Should be camel case PostScript Name NID6

NID 6: OK. No camel case required.

Error

Times New Roman Regular (times.ttf)

name

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.
Normally you should just keep it as it was in the original data (often that entry is non-existing). Just double check. It shouldn't be related to Monotype Imaging Inc! In case of concerns just give the Legal team a call and please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. You acknowledge that the font software is protected by the copyright and other intellectual property law of the United States and its various States, by the copyright and design laws of other nations, and by international treaties. Your use of this font software is limited to the rights license rights granted to you in the Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement (EULA) agreed to by you at the time of purchase and you should retain a copy of such EULA for your future reference. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. Times New Roman Italic (timesi.ttf)

name

NID 0 (0, 3, 0, 0)

'Copyright' has invalid entry.

Name table entry contains line break, but shouldn't:
'© 2017 The Monotype Corporation. All Rights Reserved. [ ][ ]Hebrew OpenType Layout logic copyright © 2003 & 2007, Ralph Hancock & John Hudson. This layout logic for Biblical Hebrew is open source software under the MIT License; see embedded license description for details.'

Error

Times New Roman Italic (timesi.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0 (0, 3, 0, 0)

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0, Copyright.

Please verify agains spec.
!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0 is '© 2017 The Monotype Corporation. All Rights Reserved. Hebrew OpenType Layout logic copyright © 2003 & 2007, Ralph Hancock & John Hudson. This layout logic for Biblical Hebrew is open source software under the MIT License; see embedded license description for details.'
It should follow this structure: 'Copyright (c) XXXX - XXXX /entity/. All rights reserved.'

Pass

name

OK: NID 1 length is '15'
'Times New Roman'

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 1

Reserved word used in Family Name NID1 and not allowed in Microsoft Office applications. Style linking and/or font embedding for MS Word won't work.

The keyword 'Roman' may cause issues in Microsoft Office applications. Style linking and/or font embedding for MS Word won't work.
(If 'Bold' has no Regular and you thought to make a single font out of it by bringing 'Bold' into NID 1 and making NID 2 to 'Regular': This cause cross platform issues in MS Word for Mac and PC. Dec. 2018)

Times New Roman Italic (timesi.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT', Everything looks good.

NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. Times New Roman Bold (timesbd.ttf)

name

NID 0 (0, 3, 0, 0)

'Copyright' has invalid entry.

Name table entry contains line break, but shouldn't:
'© 2017 The Monotype Corporation. All Rights Reserved. [ ][ ]Hebrew OpenType Layout logic copyright © 2003 & 2007, Ralph Hancock & John Hudson. This layout logic for Biblical Hebrew is open source software under the MIT License; see embedded license description for details.'

Error

Times New Roman Bold (timesbd.ttf)

name

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0 (0, 3, 0, 0)

!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0, Copyright.

Please verify agains spec.
!! BOGUS PLATFORM !! NID 0 is '© 2017 The Monotype Corporation. All Rights Reserved. Hebrew OpenType Layout logic copyright © 2003 & 2007, Ralph Hancock & John Hudson. This layout logic for Biblical Hebrew is open source software under the MIT License; see embedded license description for details.'
It should follow this structure: 'Copyright (c) XXXX - XXXX /entity/. All rights reserved.'

Pass

Times New Roman Bold (timesbd.ttf)

name

Times New Roman Bold (timesbd.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT', Everything looks good.

Times New Roman Bold (timesbd.ttf)

name

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.
Normally you should just keep it as it was in the original data (often that entry is non-existing). Just double check. It shouldn't be related to Monotype Imaging Inc! In case of concerns just give the Legal team a call and please verify against job spec.

NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. Times New Roman Bold Italic (timesbi.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItalicMT', Everything looks good.

Times New Roman Bold Italic (timesbi.ttf)

name

MS NID 7/13

License text, if Trademark (NID 7) is 'The Monotype Corporation'

License text contains 'Monotype Imaging Inc'.
Normally you should just keep it as it was in the original data (often that entry is non-existing). Just double check. It shouldn't be related to Monotype Imaging Inc! In case of concerns just give the Legal team a call and please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
NOTIFICATION OF LICENSE AGREEMENT You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype Imaging Inc., its affiliates or its licensees. You acknowledge that the font software is protected by the copyright and other intellectual property law of the United States and its various States, by the copyright and design laws of other nations, and by international treaties. Your use of this font software is limited to the rights license rights granted to you in the Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement (EULA) agreed to by you at the time of purchase and you should retain a copy of such EULA for your future reference. You may not use, rent, lease, sublicense, give, lend, or distribute the font software, or any copy thereof, except as expressly provided by the EULA. The current Monotype Imaging End User License Agreement can be viewed at http://www.fonts.com/info/legal/eula/monotype-imaging.

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Pass

Times New Roman Regular (times.ttf)

GPOS

kern

Simple check if kern feature in GPOS table.

The font has GPOS kerning.

Warning

Times New Roman Regular (times.ttf)

kern

-/-

Check if 'kern' table in TTF font.

Font has 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.
For example: PowerPoint only supports a flat GPOS kerning or a kern table. So, if the customer requires PowerPoint support, a kern table is necessary.
